<p>The Mg
 <sup>2+</sup> diffusion in the bulk active materials is one of the key parameters which determines the reaction kinetics of the magnetization/demagnetization process, here we investigated the diffusion pathways of Mg
 <sup>2+</sup> in the Mg
 <sub>3</sub>Bi
 <sub>2</sub> and the Mg
 <sub>3</sub>Sb
 <sub>2</sub>. The bond valence sum (BVS) mapping is one methodology to visualize the pathways of the mobile ions in the crystal structure. The bond-valence parameters for Mg
 <sub>3</sub>Bi
 <sub>2</sub> and Mg
 <sub>3</sub>Sb
 <sub>2</sub> were calculated by following equation (Brese and O'Keeffe, 
 <xref rid="B7" ref-type="bibr">1991</xref>). 
